3. TECHNICAL IMPLEMENTATION ARCHITECTURE

3.1 Foundation Layer: The Intelligent Data Fabric

The Seraph Stack rests on a unified data fabric that ensures consistency, availability, and integrity across all operations:

```
Data Fabric Architecture:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              SEMANTIC ABSTRACTION LAYER             │
│           (Knowledge Graphs & Ontologies)           │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│              EVENT STREAMING LAYER                  │
│     (Apache Kafka, 10M events/sec throughput)       │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│            PERSISTENCE LAYER                        │
│   (Multi-model storage with integrity proofs)       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Key Innovations:

· Temporal Consistency Guarantees: All operations maintain causality across distributed systems
· Immutable Audit Trail: Every action cryptographically signed and linked in Merkle trees
· Semantic Indexing: Data indexed by meaning, not just structure

3.2 Pillar Implementation Specifications

3.2.1 Sentinel Technical Stack

· Cryptography: Ed25519 signatures + BLS threshold signatures for distributed validation
· Machine Learning: Ensemble of Isolation Forests, LSTM networks, and Graph Neural Networks
· Policy Engine: Rego-based with WASM compilation for performance
· Performance: 1M validations/second with <150ms latency

3.2.2 Nexus Technical Stack

· Knowledge Graph: Neo4j 5.12 + TigerGraph for hybrid transactional/analytical workloads
· Translation Engine: Fine-tuned LLMs (70B parameters) with Retrieval-Augmented Generation
· Semantic Cache: Multi-level cache with semantic deduplication
· Performance: 100K translations/second with <100ms latency

3.2.3 Restor Technical Stack

· Prediction Models: Prophet + NeuralProphet hybrids with uncertainty quantification
· Causal Inference: Do-calculus implementation with counterfactual reasoning
· Optimization Engine: Multi-objective genetic algorithms with human preference learning
· Performance: 50K metrics/second analysis with 5-second diagnosis time

3.3 Deployment Architecture

The Seraph Stack supports multiple deployment models:

Cloud-Native Deployment:

```yaml
architecture: Multi-cluster Kubernetes with Istio service mesh
scaling: Horizontal pod autoscaling + cluster autoscaling
resilience: 5-nines availability with cross-region failover
```

Hybrid Edge Deployment:

```yaml
edge_nodes: Autonomous operation for 24+ hours disconnected
synchronization: CRDT-based eventual consistency
security: Hardware root of trust with TPM integration
```

Government/High-Security:

```yaml
air_gap: Full disconnected operation support
certifications: FIPS 140-3, Common Criteria EAL4+
audit: Immutable logs with third-party verifiable proofs
```

