4. SECURITY AND COMPLIANCE ARCHITECTURE

4.1 Intrinsic Security Properties

The Seraph Stack implements security as intrinsic system properties:

1. Non-Repudiation: Every action cryptographically signed by originating pillar
2. Continuous Validation: Integrity checks embedded in data flow, not batch processes
3. Least Privilege Enforcement: Dynamic permissioning based on context and need
4. Tamper Evidence: Merkle tree structures make unauthorized changes immediately detectable

4.2 Compliance Automation

The framework automates compliance across multiple regulatory regimes:

· GDPR/CCPA: Automated data subject request handling with privacy preservation
· HIPAA: PHI detection, encryption, and audit trail generation
· SOX: Continuous control monitoring with real-time exception reporting
· NIST CSF: Automated mapping of controls to implementation evidence

4.3 Quantum-Resistant Design

All cryptographic operations use post-quantum algorithms:

· Key Exchange: CRYSTALS-Kyber
· Signatures: CRYSTALS-Dilithium
· Hashing: SHA-3 with extendable output functions

